title: David Hurley - Wikipedia
snippet: General David John Hurley (born 26 August 1953) is an Australian former politician and military officer. A senior officer in the Australian Army, he served as the 27th governor-general of Australia from 2019 to 2024. He was previously the 38th governor of New South Wales from 2014 to 2019.

title: Biography - The Honourable David Hurley AC CVO DSC | Governor-General of the Commonwealth of Australia

title: David Hurley - Simple English Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia
snippet: David John Hurley AC DSC (born 26 August 1953) is an Australian former army officer. Hurley was the 27th Governor-General of Australia from 2019 to 2024. He was the Governor of New South Wales from 2014 to 2019. He had a 42-year long career in the Australian Army.

title: David Hurley (singer) - Wikipedia
snippet: David Hurley (born August 1962) is a British countertenor who sang with The King's Singers from 1990 to 2016. Hurley was a chorister at Winchester Cathedral, and a choral scholar at Winchester College and New College, Oxford.
